tasks.task: Describe the pruning process for fruit trees, focusing on key techniques and considerations.
subtasks: Explain the importance of renewing one-year-old wood for fruit production in peaches and similar trees.
Describe the open vase shape for peaches and other fruit trees, emphasizing the benefits of an open center for light and air circulation.
Discuss the process of thinning older scaffolds and removing crowded branches to maintain tree structure and promote fruit quality.
Demonstrate techniques for shaping newer fruit trees, including central leader removal and promoting outward growth of branches.
Illustrate the impact of proper pruning on disease management and fruit quality in high-humidity climates.
Offer advice on summer pruning and ongoing maintenance to address rapid tree growth and maximize light penetration.
